{
  "text": "Bueno de [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] , in a more general setting, provide models in which war can arise without uncertainty because of commitment problems. Commitment problems arise when one or the other party cannot trust the rival's statements because the rival has incentives to renege on promises.",
